max

public static VectorClock max(VectorClock pOne,
                              VectorClock pTwo)
VectorClock merging operation. Creates a new VectorClock with the maximum for each element in either clock. Used in Buffer and Process to manipulate clocks.

Parameters:
pOne - - First Clock being merged.
pTwo - - Second Clock being merged.
Returns:
A new VectorClock with the maximum for each element in either clock.

compare

public static VectorComparison compare(VectorClock pOne,
                                       VectorClock pTwo)
VectorClock compare operation. Returns one of four possible values indicating how clock one relates to clock two: VectorComparison.GREATER If One > Two. VectorComparison.EQUAL If One = Two. VectorComparison.SMALLER If One < Two. VectorComparison.SIMULTANEOUS If One <> Two.

Parameters:
pOne - - First Clock being compared.
pTwo - - Second Clock being compared.
Returns:
VectorComparison value indicating how One relates to Two.
